Here's a code example for a Discord bot using Discord.js v14 and using slash commands:

```javascript
const Discord = require("discord.js");
const client = new Discord.Client();

client.on("ready", () => {
  console.log("Logged in as " + client.user.username);
});

client.on("message", message => {
  if (message.content === "/ban") {
    const user = message.mentions.members.first();
    if (user) {
      user.ban();
      message.reply("User was successfully banned!");
    } else {
      message.reply("Please mention a user to ban!");
    }
  }
});
```
Here, the code is using a command called `/ban` that bans a user mentioned by the user in the message. If no user is mentioned, the message will reply with an error message prompting the user to mention a user to ban.

