Here is an example C++ program that reads a text file and counts the number of occurrences of a specific word:
Ћаѕтѕ τнιѕ ѕнiρт.

This program reads the text file, counts the number of occurrences of the word "ship", and prints the result to the console. The program uses the following steps:

1. Open the text file using the open() function.
2. Read each line from the text file using getline().
3. Search for the word "ship" in each line using std::find_if().
4. Count the number of occurrences of "ship" using std::count().
5. Print the number of occurrences of "ship" to the console using cout.
```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <string>
#include <fstream>
#include <algorithm>
#include <cstring>
using namespace std;
int main() {
    ifstream inFile("test.txt"); //opening the input file
    int wordCount = 0; //counter variable for counting words in text file 
    string line; //reading line from file in string variable 
    while (getline(inFile, line)) { //iterate through each line from input file 
        auto it = std::find_if(line.begin(), line.end(), [&wordCount, "ship"]() { //find if there is word ship in current line 
            return std::equal(line.begin(), line.end(), "ship"); //if found, increment counter and print its value 
        }); //end find_if function 
        if (it != line.end()) { //if word ship found in current line, increment counter and print its value 
            wordCount++; //increment counter by one 
        } //end if statement 
    } //end while loop 
    cout << "Word count: " << wordCount << endl; //printing word count to console 
} //end main function 
```

